# Constants First

All configurable values in the agentic layer must be named constants defined in `types.js`. Do not hardcode numeric or string literals inline.

## Sizes and Spacing → `AGENT_CONFIG`

```js
// ❌ Hardcoded dimensions
setNodes(nodes => nodes.concat({
  data: { width: 800, height: 400 }
}));

// ✅ Use AGENT_CONFIG
import { AGENT_CONFIG } from './types';
setNodes(nodes => nodes.concat({
  data: {
    width: AGENT_CONFIG.DEFAULT_CHART_WIDTH,
    height: AGENT_CONFIG.DEFAULT_CHART_HEIGHT,
  }
}));
```

Key `AGENT_CONFIG` values:

| Constant | Value | Use for |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `DEFAULT_CHART_WIDTH` | 800 | New chart nodes |
| `DEFAULT_CHART_HEIGHT` | 400 | New chart nodes |
| `CHART_HORIZONTAL_SPACING` | 850 | Spacing between charts |
| `CHART_VERTICAL_SPACING` | 450 | Vertical chart gaps |
| `DEFAULT_KPI_WIDTH` | 320 | KPI tile width |
| `DEFAULT_KPI_HEIGHT` | 160 | KPI tile height |
| `KPI_HORIZONTAL_SPACING` | 340 | Spacing between KPI tiles |
| `MAX_ACTIONS_PER_QUERY` | 5 | Enforced in Zod schema |

## Delays → `RATE_LIMIT_CONFIG`

```js
// ❌ Hardcoded delay
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5000));

// ✅ Use RATE_LIMIT_CONFIG
import { RATE_LIMIT_CONFIG } from './types';
await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, RATE_LIMIT_CONFIG.MEDIUM_ACTION_DELAY));
```

Key `RATE_LIMIT_CONFIG` values:

| Constant | Value | Tier |
|----------|-------|------|
| `LIGHT_ACTION_DELAY` | 3000ms | create_kpi, create_insight |
| `MEDIUM_ACTION_DELAY` | 5000ms | create_chart, ai_query |
| `HEAVY_ACTION_DELAY` | 5000ms | generate_chart_insights |
| `BACKOFF_MAX` | 30000ms | Max exponential backoff |
| `CIRCUIT_BREAKER_THRESHOLD` | 3 | Errors before circuit opens |
| `CIRCUIT_BREAKER_TIMEOUT` | 60000ms | Circuit reset window |

## Position Types → `POSITION_TYPES`

```js
// ❌ Hardcoded string
if (action.position === 'right_of_chart') { ... }

// ✅ Import the constant
import { POSITION_TYPES } from './types';
if (action.position === POSITION_TYPES.RIGHT_OF_CHART) { ... }
```

## Action Types → `ACTION_TYPES`

```js
// ❌ String literal
case 'create_chart': ...

// ✅ Constant
import { ACTION_TYPES } from './types';
case ACTION_TYPES.CREATE_CHART: ...
```

## Adding New Constants

When a value appears more than once or is likely to be tuned, add it to `types.js` first, then reference it. Do not defer — inline literals accumulate quickly.
